-- Hong Kong's Legislature Approves Proposal to Increase Its Size to 70 Seats
-- Marco Lui
-- 2010-06-25T05:29:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/hong-kong-s-legislature-approves-proposal-to-increase-its-size-to-70-seats.html

          
          
             Hong Kong’s Legislative Council
approved the government’s plan to increase its size to 70 seats
from the current 60, which Chief Executive Donald Tsang said
will push the city closer to full democracy. The 46-12 vote
today came after more than two days of debate.  
